annotationA: YKT6 v-SNARE; SNAP receptor activity; protein-cysteine S-palmitoyltransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: retrograde vesicle-mediated transport, Golgi to ER; vesicle-mediated transport; ER to Golgi vesicle-mediated transport; Belongs to the synaptobrevin family
annotationB: Vesicle-associated membrane protein 7 (Vamp7) is an R type SNARE protein. It mediates the fusion of autophagosomes with endosomes and lysosomes by forming a SNARE complex with Syx17 (Qa) and Snap29 (Qbc). Vamp7 localizes to endosomes in a Rab21 and Sbf dependent manner; Belongs to the synaptobrevin family
